# Direct runtime dependencies, the human edit surface. requirements.txt is
# the compiled, hashed, fully-pinned closure: edit here, then recompile
# (see the README test section). Pins are exact so a recompile reproduces
# the same closure rather than drifting to a newer minor.
#
# The closure is compiled under the Python floor (3.11). Cross-version
# environment markers are the known risk: a newer interpreter in the CI
# matrix could need a dependency the 3.11 compile did not pin. The matrix
# (3.11 through 3.14, installing with --require-hashes) is the standing
# proof; if a leg fails resolution, constrain the offender here and
# recompile rather than dropping the hashes.
